The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 London, Oct. 29 (PTI): Salman Rushdie has said he wants to bring out a graphic novel.           
	Recently I got asked if Id like to write a graphic novel. When I was a kid I was a real comic book nut and I can tell you a lot about superheroes, the author said.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The pilots of an Air India plane with 150 people on board aborted landing at Indira Gandhi International Airport on Thursday after experiencing fluctuations on the instrument landing system signal, but later touched down safely. None of the 143 passengers of IC-864, flying from Mumbai to Delhi, or the seven crew members was hurt.                  
	 Kathmandu (PTI): Calcutta-born Rukma Shumsher Rana will be Nepals new ambassador to India, filling a post that was vacant for about a year. Born in 1936, the son of Nepali Congress founder Subarna Shumsher Rana, had received his early education at Doon School.                   
	 Hyderabad (PTI): A 15-year-old girl hanged herself after being allegedly harassed by her school principal. Niraja, who has been arrested, had abused Vani after her brother was shifted from the school, the girls parents have alleged. Vani has accused Niraja of harassing her in her suicide note.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): The government has doubled the rail fare concessions for women police personnel decorated with the Presidents Police Medal. Policewomen over the age of 60 years will get 60 per cent discount on general fares.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): An Air India enquiry committee has chargesheeted air hostess Komal Singh, who had levelled molestation charges against two pilots, for violating the conduct rule by speaking to the media. The alleged molestation had led to a mid-air scuffle between co-pilot Aditya Chopra and flight purser Amit Khanna.
                                                                                                                           
